HEADWORD: Monothalama
<hw>Mon`o*thal"a*ma</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. Gr. <grk>mo`nos</grk> single + <grk>qa`lamos</grk> a chamber.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A division of Foraminifera including those that
have only one chamber.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

